"""
telegram_bot.py

Remote control for the yt_automation pipeline via Telegram.
Reads TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN and TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_ID from .env in the project root.

Commands:
    /start      — show available commands
    /status     — beats / rendered / uploaded counts
    /render     — run render.py (all beats) with live per-beat progress
    /batch      — render all unrendered beats with clip picker
    /seo        — run seo_metadata.py
    /upload     — upload all rendered, not-yet-uploaded videos
    /log        — show uploads_log.json entries
    /fy3stash   — pick specific beats to render by number
    /play       — listen to any beat in your stash
    /rename     — rename a beat file
    /rendering  — see what is rendering right now
    /tasks      — see all active background tasks (render + upload)
    /ghostprod  — generate a ghost-production beat brief in your style
    /melody     — send a voice note → get a MIDI melody back in your style
    /export     — convert a beat to MP3/WAV or split into stems (demucs)
    /bulktitle  — bulk edit titles (auto-generate or one by one)

File drops:
    Send any .mp3 or .wav  → saved to beats/
    Send any .mp4          → saved to images/
    Send any .jpg/.png     → saved to images/
    Send any voice note    → /melody auto-analyses it

Run:
    /Users/fyefye/yt_automation/.venv/bin/python3.14 telegram_bot.py
"""

